The paper deals with algorithmic properties of split decomposition, a graph decomposition technique, and uses graph-labelled trees as a combinatorial object to simplify its consideration. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions circle graph recognition, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph algorithms (cs.DL). Finally, the paper also discusses Lexicographic Breadth-First Search (LBFS), which is a graph traversal algorithm, indicating a possible connection to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
